  <h2 id="transducers-and-instrumentation-lab">Transducers and Instrumentation Lab</h2>
  <hr />
  <p>Welcome to the course page for Transducers and Instrumentation theory and lab courses. This page contains all course realted information. For all course related queries please contact the course <a href="mailto:siva82kb@cmcvellore.ac.in">instructor</a>.</p>

  <h3 id="course-information-document">Course Information Document</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Theory</strong>: <a href="https://github.com/siva82kb/teaching/raw/master/transducers_and_instrumentation/info/course_info.pdf">Course Info</a></li>
    <li><strong>Lab</strong>: Course Info</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="theory-lecture-timings">[Theory] Lecture timings</h3>
  <p>Mondays and Tuesday: 9:00AM to 10:30AM</p>

  <h3 id="lab-timings">Lab timings</h3>
  <p>Tue: 2:00PM - 5:00PM, Sat: 9:00AM - 12:00PM</p>

  <h3 id="course-modules">Course Modules</h3>
  <h4 id="module-01-introduction-to-measurement">Module 01: Introduction to measurement</h4>
  <h6 id="measurement-measuring-instrument-transducer--sensors-generalized-static-characteristics-of-sensors-generalized-dynamic-characteristics-error-analysis-sampling">Measurement; Measuring instrument; Transducer &amp; sensors; Generalized static characteristics of sensors; Generalized dynamic characteristics; Error analysis; Sampling</h6>

  <h4 id="module-02-analog-signal-processing">Module 02: Analog Signal Processing</h4>
  <p>Operational amplifier; Linear circuits with op-amps; First order and second order filters. System identification.</p>

  <h4 id="module-03-measuring-movements-linear-and-rotational">Module 03: Measuring movements: linear and rotational</h4>
  <p>Resistive; Inductive; Capacitive; Digital sensors; Camera based tracking; Accelerometer; Gyroscope.</p>

  <h4 id="module-04-measuring-effort-force-and-torque">Module 04: Measuring effort: Force and Torque</h4>
  <p>Strain gauge; Piezoelectric sensors.</p>

  <h4 id="module-05-measuring-pressure-flow-volume">Module 05: Measuring pressure, flow, volume.</h4>
  <p>Different pressure, flow, and volume sensing methods.</p>

  <h4 id="module-06-measuring-temperature">Module 06: Measuring temperature.</h4>
  <p>Thermocouple; Thermistor; Radiation thermometry.</p>

  <h4 id="module-07-measuring-biopotentials">Module 07: Measuring biopotentials</h4>
  <p>Origins of biopotentials; Review of basic electrochemistry; Electrode half-potentials; Electrical equivalent circuits of electrodes.</p>

  <h4 id="module-08-measuring-chemicals">Module 08: Measuring chemicals</h4>
  <p>pH sensor; Oxygen and Cardon dioxide sensors; Glucose sensors.</p>

